ased on a 30-day month. If the billing demand is less than 25 kW for 12 consecutive months, you have the option to transfer to Small \nGeneral Service.\n• Service at Higher Voltages The above prices except for the Energy Charge Credit are reduced \nby the following Voltage Discounts:\nPer kW Per kWh Primary $0.80 $0.00105\nTransmission Transformed $1.55 $0.00267\nTransmission $2.35 $0.00277\nOptional electric services  ...    June through September......................$0.07919\nOctober through May........................... $0.06814 Basic service charge.................................... $29.64\nOn-peak period demand charge per kW: June through September..........................$14.79\nOctober through May................................$10.49 Off-peak demand in excess of\nOn-Peak Period Demand per kW................$2.35\nEnergy charge per kWh: On-peak................................................$0.04855  ...    Energy charge credit.................................$0.01518\nIf service is other than Secondary Voltage, General Service Voltage Discounts are applicable \nto the above prices except for the Energy Charge Credit. Billing demand adjustments also apply to \nthis optional service.\n*Mandatory for very large customers (over 1000 kW demand).\nAutomatic protective lighting service prices –\noptional service  ...    100 Watt Area Lighting................................................................$7.41  ...    charges. The Minnesota Public Utilities Commission reviews\nthese annually. \nAffordability surcharge  ...    Call the Xcel Energy Business Solutions Center at 800.481.4700 for complete rate schedules, terms and conditions for all electric\nrate services.\nHow to reach us Minnesota electric and gas\n24-Hour Emergency  ...    Xcel Energy"
