ging energy demand – affect the cost of producing electricity, and, in turn, the price you pay. We continuously balance these factors to ensure reliable electricity, cleaner energy and the best price possible for  ...    The largest single component of your bill is fuel costs. Xcel Energy makes no profit on this portion of your bill since  ...    electric bills. Our wind farms saved customers billions in avoided fuel costs and tax credits across our corporate service area. - Contracting for wholesale natural gas purchases before winter to lock in lower prices. - Purchasing and storing natural gas ahead of the winter heating season when prices are lower. - Adding more clean energy to the grid, because wind and solar generate electricity without fuel costs. - New Mexico Rule Tariffs Rule No. 1, Rev. 1 - General Statement of Purpose (Sept 8, 2008) (PDF) Rule No. 2, Rev. 2 - Definitions (Apr 5, 2014) (PDF) Rule No. 3, Rev. 1 - Application for Service (Sept 8, 2008) (PDF) Rule No. 4, Rev. 1 - Supplying of Service (Sept 8, 2008) (PDF) Rule No. 5, Org - Character of Service (Aug 30, 1985)  ...    (PDF) Rule No. 30, Rev 1 - Community Solar Subscriber Consent Form (May 31, 2025) (PDF) # Rate Books Access our current rate books based on your service area, which include basic information on rates, rate adjustments, and other helpful details. ## Electric Rate Book Section 1 - Table of Contents (PDF) Section 2 - Contact List (PDF) [Section 3 - Service Area"
