        " North Dakota approves Xcel electricity rate increase\n######\nBy: Jeff Beach\n-\nFebruary 5, 2026\n4:33 pm\n\n**\n\n\n**\n\n\n**\n\n\n**\n\n[  ...    ** Randy Christmann, chair of the North Dakota Public Service Commission, speaks to a representative of Xcel Energy  ...    Utility regulators on Thursday approved a compromise electricity rate increase for North Dakota customers of Xcel Energy, a deal they say shields those rate-payers from subsidizing renewable energy projects in Minnesota. Northern States Power Co., part of Minnesota-based Xcel Energy, in 2024 asked the North Dakota Public Service Commission for an electric rate increase of 19.34% with the residential rate increasing by more than 24%. Xcel Energy agreed to cut its proposed electricity rate increase for North Dakota customers. The agreement raises overall rates by 10.37%, with the increase for residential customers at 12.92%. North Dakota customers have already been paying a higher electric rate this year under an interim rate increase. An  ...    Xcel had not asked for a rate increase in four years, which a company representative said was needed to address high  ...    > Xcel cuts electric rate increase for North Dakota customers in half\n Xcel has about 97,000 customers in North Dakota, including in Fargo, Grand Forks and Minot. Commission Chair Randy Christmann said the agreement reached with Xcel means that North Dakota customers will not be paying for what he called “green new deal” facilities in Minnesota. The agreement lists 23 facilities — mostly wind and solar projects — that are excluded from cost-recovery.  ...    AARP, which filed a comment with the PSC objecting to the initial rate increase request, said Thursday it was glad the  ...    Director Josh Askvig said. Minnesota has been pushing utilities away from fossil fuels such as coal. Xcel is retiring coal-fired power plants in Minnesota earlier than North Dakota regulators anticipated. Earlier in the meeting, the PSC approved extending a permit for mining coal at the Freedom Mine near Beulah.  ...    1\nX\n# North Dakota approves Xcel electricity rate increase\nby Jeff Beach, North Dakota Monitor February 5, 2026\n<h1>North Dakota approves Xcel electricity rate increase</h1> <p>by Jeff Beach, <a href=\"https://northdakotamonitor.com\">North Dakota Monitor</a> <br />February 5, 2026</p> <p>Utility regulators on Thursday approved a compromise electricity rate increase for North Dakota customers of Xcel Energy, a deal they say shields those rate-payers from subsidizing renewable energy projects in  ...    <p>Northern States Power Co., part of Minnesota-based Xcel Energy, in 2024 asked the North Dakota Public Service  ...    href=\"https://northdakotamonitor.com/2025/12/01/xcel-cuts-electric-rate-increase-for-north-dakota-customers-in-half/\"&g  ...    d/#?secret=oS2sPxaCU2#?secret=rDENpwoYMY\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p> <p>Xcel has about 97,000 customers in North Dakota, including in Fargo, Grand Forks and Minot.</p> <p>Commission Chair Randy Christmann said the agreement reached with Xcel means that North Dakota customers will  ...    <p>AARP, which filed a comment with the PSC objecting to the initial rate increase request, said Thursday it was  ...    <p>Minnesota has been pushing utilities away from fossil fuels such as coal. Xcel is <a href=\"https://northdakotamonitor.com/2025/10/06/xcels-coal-exit-an-issue-in-north-dakota-electric-rate-case/\">retiri ng coal-fired power plants</a> in Minnesota earlier than North Dakota regulators anticipated.</p> <p>"
